This paper deals with the problem of estimating the cardinality of a stream, which is a common problem in database systems. Therefore, cs.DB (Databases) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new method using data structures, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The method involves using machine learning techniques to estimate the cardinality, which could be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper also involves some information theory concepts, which could be classified under cs.IT (Information Theory).
